Installation of MongoDB (Windows)
Introduction

MongoDB is a NoSQL database that stores data in JSON-like format (BSON). It is widely used for modern web applications due to its flexibility and scalability.

Step 1: Download MongoDB

Open a web browser.

Visit the official MongoDB website: https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community

Select:

Version: Latest Stable Version

Platform: Windows

Package: MSI

Click Download to download the installer file.

Step 2: Install MongoDB

Open the downloaded .msi file.

Click Next in the setup wizard.

Accept the License Agreement and click Next.

Choose Complete setup type (recommended).

Ensure that Install MongoDB as a Service is selected.

Click Next, then click Install.

Wait for installation to complete.

Click Finish.

Step 3: Install MongoDB Shell (mongosh)

Go to https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/shell

Select Windows and download the MSI installer.

Run the installer and follow the setup instructions.

Click Finish after installation.

Step 4: Verify MongoDB Installation

Press Windows + R, type cmd, and press Enter.

Type the following command:

mongosh

If installed successfully, it will connect to:

mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017

You will see the MongoDB shell prompt.

Step 5: Test MongoDB

Inside the MongoDB shell, type:

show dbs

This command displays the list of databases.

To create a new database:

use myDatabase

To exit the shell:

exit
